    <h1>Forum Rules</h1>

    <h4>1. Respect and Civility</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Treat all members with respect, regardless of their opinions or background.</li>
        <li>No personal attacks, insults, or ad hominem arguments.</li>
        <li>Disagree with ideas, not people.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>2. Quality Contributions</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Strive to add value to every discussion you participate in.</li>
        <li>Back up claims with evidence or logical reasoning when possible.</li>
        <li>Stay on topic and avoid derailing threads.</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>3. Intellectual Honesty</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>Be open to changing your mind when presented with compelling evidence or arguments.</li>
        <li>Don't misrepresent others' arguments (avoid straw man fallacies).</li>
    </ul>



    <p class="remember">Remember: The goal is to foster an environment where ideas can be exchanged freely, respectfully, and productively. By following these rules, we can create a space for meaningful dialogue and collective growth.</p>
